K
|\det(A)-\det(B)|\leq K||A-B||_F
A,B\in \mathcal{C}^{n\times n}
|\det(A)-\det(B)|\leq K||A-B||_F^\alpha
K
\alpha
n = 1
n > 1
\alpha
\alpha \in (0,1]
\lvert \det (r\cdot I) - \det (0\cdot I)\rvert = \lvert r^n\rvert = \lVert I\rVert_F^{-1}\cdot\lvert r\rvert^{n-\alpha}\cdot \lVert r\cdot I - 0\rVert_F^\alpha,
\lvert r\rvert^{n-\alpha}
|\det A|
A[0,1]^n
A
A=(a_1,a_2,..., a_n)
 |\det(A)| \le  \|a_1\|\,\|a_2\|\,....\,\|a_n\| \le  \left(\frac{\|a_1\|^2+\|a_2\|^2+....+\|a_n\|^2}{n}\right)^{\frac{n}{2}} = \left(\frac{\|A\|_F^2}{n}\right)^{\frac{n}{2}} =\frac{\|A\|_F^n}{n^{n/2}} 
